{"title_page": "Jean-Marc Savelli", "text_new": "{{short description|French musician (born 1955)}}\n{{copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Jean-Marc Savelli\n| image            = Jean Marc SAVELLI Pianist.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = Savelli in a recording studio\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date|1955|10|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Mulhouse, Alsace]], France\n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| genre            = [[Classical music|Classical]]\n| occupation       = Pianist\n| instrument       = [[Piano]]\n| years_active     = <!-- YYYY\u2013YYYY (or \u2013present) -->\n| website          = {{url|www.jmsavelli.com/}}\n}}\n'''Jean-Marc Savelli''' (born 18 October 1955) is a French [[pianist]].<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_c\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jean-marc%20savelli_biographie.pdf |title=Jean Marc Savelli : Resume |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\n\nPublicly recognized for his interpretations of works by [[Franz Liszt]], [[Frederic Chopin]], the classical repertoire of [[Johann Sebastian Bach]] and [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], as well as the Impressionist repertoire of [[Claude Debussy]].<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |title=recital JM SAVELLI Pianiste-Concertiste le virtuose de l'Emotion |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref name=\"ladepeche\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2000/08/09/142108-le-cabardes-va-piano.html|title=Le Cabard\u00e8s va piano - 09/08/2000|date=|publisher=Ladepeche.fr|accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref name=\"youtube_a\">{{YouTube|_bZm1P9EeSU|JM Savelli plays the pr\u00e9lude 2 opus 3}} de [[Sergue\u00ef Rachmaninov]] \u00e0 la [[salle Gaveau]]</ref><ref name=\"youtube_b\">{{YouTube|vSe_MZ0khKI|JM Savelli plays \"R\u00eave d'amour\"}} de Franz Liszt \u00e0 la [[salle Gaveau]] (Paris)</ref><ref name=\"chaumiereonline\">{{cite web|url=http://www.chaumiereonline.com/Musique-Classique/Page-Resultat-Recherche.aspx?type=1&rch=savelli|title=Archived copy|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130102120346/http://www.chaumiereonline.com/Musique-Classique/Page-Resultat-Recherche.aspx?type=1&rch=savelli|archivedate=2013-01-02|accessdate=2012-08-31}}</ref><ref name=\"youtube_c\">{{YouTube|IaCGavCd1-s|JM Savelli joue \"Les fun\u00e9railles\" de Franz Liszt}}</ref>\n\n==Biography ==\nBorn in [[Mulhouse, Alsace]], France, to an Alsatian mother, Marie-Louise Schreyer, coming from a musical family of traveling musicians who performed in Eastern Europe, including in front of the Imperial Court of [[Russia]], and a [[Corsica|Corsican]] father, Gratien Savelli. {{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nJM Savelli was admitted at the age of 8 years to the [[National Conservatory of Music and Dramatic Art of Mulhouse]]. After receiving a first prize award at the age of 12 {{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}, he was admitted to the  [[National Conservatory of Music (Basel)]]. {{CN|date=April 2020}}. After graduating from the Basel conservatory, he studied with the pianist Master [[Pierre Sancan]]<ref name=\"musimem\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musimem.com/prix-rome-1940-1949.htm |title=Prix de Rome 1940-1949 |publisher=Musimem.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref> and was admitted to the [[Conservatoire de Paris|Conservatoire National Superieur de Musique in Paris (CNSMD)]].<ref name=\"jmsavelli\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jmsavelli.com/ |title=recital JM SAVELLI Pianiste-Concertiste le virtuose de l'Emotion |publisher=Jmsavelli.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_d\">{{cite web |url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/MOT_DE_M_LA_BRUCHOLLERIE_SUR_DIPLOME_JMSAVELLI.pdf |title=Orange |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 }}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAfter a series of concerts in the world,<ref name=\"musique-corse\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musique-corse.com/cat.php?idcat=97 |title=Corse, musique en Corse, vente disques de musique corse |publisher=Musique-corse.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>  Jean Marc Savelli momentarily stopped his career but not the piano, for family reasons, and he continued to practice piano.<ref name=\"medecines-douces\">{{cite web|url=http://medecines-douces.eu/therapie/content/musicoth%C3%A9rapie-musico-stressologie-et-grand-pr%C3%A9matur%C3%A9 |title=Musicoth\u00e9rapie, Musico-Stressologie et Grand Pr\u00e9matur\u00e9 &#124; Th\u00e9rapies Int\u00e9gratives, Hypnose Ericksonienne, Ost\u00e9opathie, Sophrologie, Paris |publisher=Medecines-douces.eu |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\nIt was during this time that he devoted himself to the influence of music on people,<ref name=\"affinitiz\">{{cite web|url=http://affinitiz.net/space/aecouterelax/content/_FDD880A5-F325-4D48-BB23-D159DC98D232 |accessdate=August 20, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111162704/http://affinitiz.net/space/aecouterelax/content/_FDD880A5-F325-4D48-BB23-D159DC98D232 |archivedate=November 11, 2013 }}</ref> and primarily for those who suffer.<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_b\">{{cite web |url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/affiche_2005_sorbonne_conference_nouvelle_adresse.pdf |title=Orange |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 }}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nHe embodies his research with the help of doctors, by the establishment of an emotional level, usable by anyone other than the musicians.<ref name=\"medecines-douces_a\">{{cite web|url=http://medecines-douces.eu/therapie/content/la-musico-stressologie%C2%A9-cr%C3%A9%C3%A9e-par-j-m-savelli |title=La Musico-Stressologie\u00a9 cr\u00e9\u00e9e par J-M. Savelli &#124; Th\u00e9rapies Int\u00e9gratives, Hypnose Ericksonienne, Ost\u00e9opathie, Sophrologie, Paris |publisher=Medecines-douces.eu |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\nDuring and after 2012, Jean Marc Savelli prepared his coming back of concerts devoted to Beethoven-Chopin-Liszt. He was expected back on the scene in 2013.\n\nIn 2013, he came back with an original video clip \"Corse Classique\" dedicated to [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], [[Franz Liszt]], and [[Frederic Chopin]].<ref>{{YouTube|id=gXIChwW9vOA#t=148|title=\"Corse Classique\", produced by the studio Ricordu}}</ref> This video was voted best YouTube video about [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] by musicsense.org<ref name=\"musicsense.org\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/musicsense.org.jpg |title=Beethoven - Emotion Classique |publisher=Musicsense.org |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref> for the interpretation of Jean-Marc SAVELLI of the [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)|Piano Sonata No. 8]] (\"Path\u00e9tique\") of [[Ludwig van Beethoven]].\n\nIn 2014 he presented his new album \"CLASSICAL RECITAL\", (American) Label \"FAMOUS RECORDS CORP.\"<ref name=\"famousmusicgroup.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.famousmusicgroup.com/ |title=famous-records |publisher=Famousmusicgroup.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810012308/http://www.famousmusicgroup.com/ |archive-date=2014-08-10 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"amazon.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Classical-Recital-Jean-Marc-Savelli/dp/B00LBUVT9Y |title=Classical Recital: Jean-Marc Savelli: MP3 Downloads |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\n\nThe website \"zippyshare\" positioned Jean-Marc in the top 1000 artists playing Beethoven and placing Jean-Marc Savelli between Wilhelm Kempff and Vladimir Horowitz,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=beethoven |title=beethoven Music Genre - Zippy Download Free ZippyShare Mp3 Download |publisher=ZippyShare.eu |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105132602/http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=beethoven# |archive-date=2015-01-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> \nand NUMBER ONE in the TOP 1000 for his performances in [[Franz Liszt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=liszt |title=liszt Music Genre - Zippy Download Free ZippyShare Mp3 Download |publisher=ZippyShare.eu |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105132614/http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=liszt# |archive-date=2015-01-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jms_n1%20liszt.JPG</ref>\n\nHe was also ranked in the TOP 12 GLOBAL PIANISTS Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin interpreters by edu.gazeta.pl.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edu.gazeta.pl/edu/h/Pianista |title=Pianista - w encyklopedii online |language=pl |publisher=Edu.gazeta.pl |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref>http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jm_savelli.JPG</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n1989 ALBUM,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fptgeBULc5g&list=OLAK5uy_m3eYQ3AENODsPUofKLejsbc-n8bbX8Pf4</ref> \nAlbum archived on the famous National Library of France (\"Biblioth\u00e8que Nationale de France\" BNF)<ref name=\"data.bnf.fr\">https://data.bnf.fr/fr/13962815/jean-marc_savelli/</ref>\n\n[[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]] \n* Mazurka No 1 op 7\n* Mazurka n\u00b02 op7\n* Mazurka n\u00b04 op17\n* Mazurka n\u00b02 op68\n* Mazurka n\u00b04 op67\n* Polonaise n\u00b01 op26\n* Polonaise n\u00b01 op40\n* Polonaise n\u00b02 op40\n* Polonaise in A-flat major, Op. 53 \"Heroic Polonaise\"<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=liODMUIXUtI</ref>\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 15 op 28\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 4 op 28\n\n[[Ludwig van Beethoven]]\n* Piano Sonata No. 8 in C minor, Op. 13, commonly known as Sonata Path\u00e9tique\n* 1st movement<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uIzJE8o2QZo</ref>\n* 2nd movement<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l81BAZgSCUE</ref>\n* 3rd movement<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TY2wYBm2AFw</ref>\n\n[[Sergei Rachmaninov]]\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 2 op 3<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_bZm1P9EeSU</ref>\n\n[[Franz Liszt]]\n* Fun\u00e9railles n\u00b05<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IaCGavCd1-s</ref>\n* Rhapsodie hongroise n\u00b02<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NMAUDorDlNk</ref>\n* Mephisto Walse n\u00b01\n\n[[Robert Schumann]]\n* Reverie\n\n2014 album \"CLASSICAL RECITAL\", on label \"FAMOUS RECORDS Corp\"<ref name=\"famousmusicgroup.com\"/><ref name=\"amazon.com\"/><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJXnAyICU34&list=OLAK5uy_nRnuwzKgFSSyDydYcG0uxMW6fwYTJw3AM</ref><ref>https://music.amazon.co.uk/artists/B00LCAZS04?tab=CATALOG&ref=dm_wcp_artist_link_ad</ref>\n\n* [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)]]\n* [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]] [[Polonaise in A-flat major, Op. 53 (Chopin)]]\n* [[Andersen Viana]], Primeira Neo Valsa<ref>https://www.amazon.fr/Vianas-Primeira-Neo-Valsa-Version/dp/B00LBPMDIA/ref=sr_1_5?s=dmusic&ie=UTF8&qid=1440703232&sr=1-5&keywords=Jean-Marc+Savelli</ref>\n* [[Franz Liszt]] Rhapsodie hongroise No. 2\n\n2014 album \"The PIANIST of EMOTION\" on label \"KDM\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.mnet.interest.me/album/359895 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123081834/http://m.mnet.interest.me/album/359895 |archive-date=2015-11-23 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>https://www.amazon.fr/Classical-Recital-Jean-Marc-Savelli/dp/B00LBPM74U</ref><ref>https://www.genie.co.kr/detail/albumInfo?axnm=80453414</ref>\n[[Ludwig van Beethoven]], [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]], [[Andersen Viana]], [[Franz Liszt]]\n\nMusical works interpreted by Savelli are in French heritage within the [[National Library of France]] BNF.<ref name=\"data.bnf.fr\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n1981   Invited by [[Tino Rossi]] <ref>https://doc-14-1o-apps-viewer.googleusercontent.com/viewer/secure/pdf/26ank84sohj67791ulafelbljmg70fq2/tm74010vsibt6gr5kc5de3cs4q04v73l/1586182050000/drive/09855480875314119482/ACFrOgAalYCGIN9yCIXyjq6Q2l2kziKopvUEUXsLAhL8Rj-jNPuMFut--AiCTwdq6YQ2fK7te44ykdKkaNc-dqR5TIZvB17hPS-Jwt2SYjzKJJ5_ZrbxqNlJUB9t8JLwjQzyz2PBnfzvvzSuddZS?print=true&nonce=d78ivt4e4b16m&user=09855480875314119482&hash=mvhtj5u0gg4fv6icbfvndjrj673ajfat </ref>, in the television program Jacques Chancel's \"Great Chessboard\" on January 29, 1981, Jean-Marc Savelli interpreted  Sadness <ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1490460/?ref_=nmbio_bio_nm</ref> (Study Op. 10, n \u00b0 3, in E major) by [[Frederic Chopin]].\n\n\n2013  \"Corse Classique\" dedicated to [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], [[Franz Liszt]], [[Frederic Chopin]],<ref>{{YouTube|id=gXIChwW9vOA#t=148|title=\"Corse Classique\", clip video by Jean-Marc Savelli produced by the studio Ricordu}}</ref> voted best YouTube video about [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] by musicsense.org for the interpretation of Savelli in the 2nd and 3rd movement of the [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)|Piano Sonata No. 8]] of [[Ludwig van Beethoven]].\n\n==Bibliography==\n2020 \"French piano legends\"<ref>http://www.musicae.fr/livre-Les-Legendes-francaises-du-piano-de-Catherine-Lechner-Reydellet-226-135.html</ref>\nby [[Catherine Lechner-Reydellet]]<ref>https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catherine_Lechner-Reydellet</ref>\n\n\"French legends of the piano\" aux Editions [[Aedam Musicae]], published in 2020, is a work by [[Catherine Lechner-Reydellet]] [[writer]], and [[pianist]] dedicated to the memory of French pianists of the 20th century. Its vocation is to discover what the masters of the past have left to the great performers who succeeded them and in particular to decipher the technique of the ancients thanks to witnesses to French legends; we find Jean-Marc Savelli there through the heritage received from his masters [[Yvonne Lefebure]], [[Monique de La Bruchollerie]] and [[Pierre Sancan]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|france}}\n\n==links==\n*[http://www.musimem.com/prix-rome-1940-1949.htm Biographie Sancan]\n*[http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/ Official website JM SAVELLI]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Savelli, Jean-Marc}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:French classical pianists]]\n[[Category:French male pianists]]\n[[Category:Conservatoire de Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Mulhouse]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical pianists]]\n[[Category:21st-century French male musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French musician (born 1955)}}\n{{copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Jean-Marc Savelli\n| image            = Jean Marc SAVELLI Pianist.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = Savelli prepare his album\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date|1955|10|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Mulhouse, Alsace]], France\n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| genre            = [[Classical music|Classical]]\n| occupation       = Pianist\n| instrument       = [[Piano]]\n| years_active     = <!-- YYYY\u2013YYYY (or \u2013present) -->\n| website =  {{url|www.jmsavelli.com/}}\n}}\n'''Jean-Marc Savelli''' (born 18 October 1955) is a French [[pianist]].<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_c\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jean-marc%20savelli_biographie.pdf |title=Jean Marc Savelli : Resume |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\n\nPublicly recognized for his interpretations of works by [[Franz Liszt]], [[Frederic Chopin]], the classical repertoire of [[Johann Sebastian Bach]] and [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], as well as the Impressionist repertoire of [[Claude Debussy]].<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |title=recital JM SAVELLI Pianiste-Concertiste le virtuose de l'Emotion |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref name=\"ladepeche\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2000/08/09/142108-le-cabardes-va-piano.html|title=Le Cabard\u00e8s va piano - 09/08/2000|date=|publisher=Ladepeche.fr|accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref name=\"youtube_a\">{{YouTube|_bZm1P9EeSU|JM Savelli plays the pr\u00e9lude 2 opus 3}} de [[Sergue\u00ef Rachmaninov]] \u00e0 la [[salle Gaveau]]</ref><ref name=\"youtube_b\">{{YouTube|vSe_MZ0khKI|JM Savelli plays \"R\u00eave d'amour\"}} de Franz Liszt \u00e0 la [[salle Gaveau]] (Paris)</ref><ref name=\"chaumiereonline\">{{cite web|url=http://www.chaumiereonline.com/Musique-Classique/Page-Resultat-Recherche.aspx?type=1&rch=savelli|title=Archived copy|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130102120346/http://www.chaumiereonline.com/Musique-Classique/Page-Resultat-Recherche.aspx?type=1&rch=savelli|archivedate=2013-01-02|accessdate=2012-08-31}}</ref><ref name=\"youtube_c\">{{YouTube|IaCGavCd1-s|JM Savelli joue \"Les fun\u00e9railles\" de Franz Liszt}}</ref>\n\n==Biography ==\nBorn in [[Mulhouse, Alsace]], France, to an Alsatian mother, Marie-Louise Schreyer, coming from a musical family of traveling musicians who performed in Eastern Europe, including in front of the Imperial Court of [[Russia]], and a [[Corsica|Corsican]] father, Gratien Savelli. {{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nJM Savelli was admitted at the age of 8 years to the [[National Conservatory of Music and Dramatic Art of Mulhouse]]. After receiving a first prize award at the age of 12 {{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}, he was admitted to the  [[National Conservatory of Music (Basel)]]. {{CN|date=April 2020}}. After graduating from the Basel conservatory, he studied with the pianist Master [[Pierre Sancan]]<ref name=\"musimem\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musimem.com/prix-rome-1940-1949.htm |title=Prix de Rome 1940-1949 |publisher=Musimem.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref> and was admitted to the [[Conservatoire de Paris|Conservatoire National Superieur de Musique in Paris (CNSMD)]].<ref name=\"jmsavelli\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jmsavelli.com/ |title=recital JM SAVELLI Pianiste-Concertiste le virtuose de l'Emotion |publisher=Jmsavelli.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_d\">{{cite web |url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/MOT_DE_M_LA_BRUCHOLLERIE_SUR_DIPLOME_JMSAVELLI.pdf |title=Orange |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 }}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAfter a series of concerts in the world,<ref name=\"musique-corse\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musique-corse.com/cat.php?idcat=97 |title=Corse, musique en Corse, vente disques de musique corse |publisher=Musique-corse.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>  Jean Marc Savelli momentarily stopped his career but not the piano, for family reasons, and he continued to practice piano.<ref name=\"medecines-douces\">{{cite web|url=http://medecines-douces.eu/therapie/content/musicoth%C3%A9rapie-musico-stressologie-et-grand-pr%C3%A9matur%C3%A9 |title=Musicoth\u00e9rapie, Musico-Stressologie et Grand Pr\u00e9matur\u00e9 &#124; Th\u00e9rapies Int\u00e9gratives, Hypnose Ericksonienne, Ost\u00e9opathie, Sophrologie, Paris |publisher=Medecines-douces.eu |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\nIt was during this time that he devoted himself to the influence of music on people,<ref name=\"affinitiz\">{{cite web|url=http://affinitiz.net/space/aecouterelax/content/_FDD880A5-F325-4D48-BB23-D159DC98D232 |accessdate=August 20, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111162704/http://affinitiz.net/space/aecouterelax/content/_FDD880A5-F325-4D48-BB23-D159DC98D232 |archivedate=November 11, 2013 }}</ref> and primarily for those who suffer.<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_b\">{{cite web |url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/affiche_2005_sorbonne_conference_nouvelle_adresse.pdf |title=Orange |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 }}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nHe embodies his research with the help of doctors, by the establishment of an emotional level, usable by anyone other than the musicians.<ref name=\"medecines-douces_a\">{{cite web|url=http://medecines-douces.eu/therapie/content/la-musico-stressologie%C2%A9-cr%C3%A9%C3%A9e-par-j-m-savelli |title=La Musico-Stressologie\u00a9 cr\u00e9\u00e9e par J-M. Savelli &#124; Th\u00e9rapies Int\u00e9gratives, Hypnose Ericksonienne, Ost\u00e9opathie, Sophrologie, Paris |publisher=Medecines-douces.eu |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\nDuring and after 2012, Jean Marc Savelli prepared his coming back of concerts devoted to Beethoven-Chopin-Liszt. He was expected back on the scene in 2013.\n\nIn 2013, he came back with an original video clip \"Corse Classique\" dedicated to [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], [[Franz Liszt]], and [[Frederic Chopin]].<ref>{{YouTube|id=gXIChwW9vOA#t=148|title=\"Corse Classique\", produced by the studio Ricordu}}</ref> This video was voted best YouTube video about [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] by musicsense.org<ref name=\"musicsense.org\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/musicsense.org.jpg |title=Beethoven - Emotion Classique |publisher=Musicsense.org |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref> for the interpretation of Jean-Marc SAVELLI of the [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)|Piano Sonata No. 8]] (\"Path\u00e9tique\") of [[Ludwig van Beethoven]].\n\nIn 2014 he presented his new album \"CLASSICAL RECITAL\", (American) Label \"FAMOUS RECORDS CORP.\"<ref name=\"famousmusicgroup.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.famousmusicgroup.com/ |title=famous-records |publisher=Famousmusicgroup.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810012308/http://www.famousmusicgroup.com/ |archive-date=2014-08-10 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"amazon.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Classical-Recital-Jean-Marc-Savelli/dp/B00LBUVT9Y |title=Classical Recital: Jean-Marc Savelli: MP3 Downloads |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\n\nThe website \"zippyshare\" positioned Jean-Marc in the top 1000 artists playing Beethoven and placing Jean-Marc Savelli between Wilhelm Kempff and Vladimir Horowitz,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=beethoven |title=beethoven Music Genre - Zippy Download Free ZippyShare Mp3 Download |publisher=ZippyShare.eu |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105132602/http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=beethoven# |archive-date=2015-01-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> \nand NUMBER ONE in the TOP 1000 for his performances in [[Franz Liszt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=liszt |title=liszt Music Genre - Zippy Download Free ZippyShare Mp3 Download |publisher=ZippyShare.eu |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105132614/http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=liszt# |archive-date=2015-01-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jms_n1%20liszt.JPG</ref>\n\nHe was also ranked in the TOP 12 GLOBAL PIANISTS Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin interpreters by edu.gazeta.pl.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edu.gazeta.pl/edu/h/Pianista |title=Pianista - w encyklopedii online |language=pl |publisher=Edu.gazeta.pl |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref>http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jm_savelli.JPG</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n1989 ALBUM,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fptgeBULc5g&list=OLAK5uy_m3eYQ3AENODsPUofKLejsbc-n8bbX8Pf4</ref> \nAlbum archived on the famous National Library of France (\"Biblioth\u00e8que Nationale de France\" BNF)<ref name=\"data.bnf.fr\">https://data.bnf.fr/fr/13962815/jean-marc_savelli/</ref>\n\n[[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]] \n* Mazurka No 1 op 7\n* Mazurka n\u00b02 op7\n* Mazurka n\u00b04 op17\n* Mazurka n\u00b02 op68\n* Mazurka n\u00b04 op67\n* Polonaise n\u00b01 op26\n* Polonaise n\u00b01 op40\n* Polonaise n\u00b02 op40\n* Polonaise in A-flat major, Op. 53 \"Heroic Polonaise\"<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=liODMUIXUtI</ref>\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 15 op 28\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 4 op 28\n\n[[Ludwig van Beethoven]]\n* Piano Sonata No. 8 in C minor, Op. 13, commonly known as Sonata Path\u00e9tique\n* 1st movement<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uIzJE8o2QZo</ref>\n* 2nd movement<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l81BAZgSCUE</ref>\n* 3rd movement<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TY2wYBm2AFw</ref>\n\n[[Sergei Rachmaninov]]\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 2 op 3<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_bZm1P9EeSU</ref>\n\n[[Franz Liszt]]\n* Fun\u00e9railles n\u00b05<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IaCGavCd1-s</ref>\n* Rhapsodie hongroise n\u00b02<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NMAUDorDlNk</ref>\n* Mephisto Walse n\u00b01\n\n[[Robert Schumann]]\n* Reverie\n\n2014 album \"CLASSICAL RECITAL\", on label \"FAMOUS RECORDS Corp\"<ref name=\"famousmusicgroup.com\"/><ref name=\"amazon.com\"/><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJXnAyICU34&list=OLAK5uy_nRnuwzKgFSSyDydYcG0uxMW6fwYTJw3AM</ref><ref>https://music.amazon.co.uk/artists/B00LCAZS04?tab=CATALOG&ref=dm_wcp_artist_link_ad</ref>\n\n* [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)]]\n* [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]] [[Polonaise in A-flat major, Op. 53 (Chopin)]]\n* [[Andersen Viana]], Primeira Neo Valsa<ref>https://www.amazon.fr/Vianas-Primeira-Neo-Valsa-Version/dp/B00LBPMDIA/ref=sr_1_5?s=dmusic&ie=UTF8&qid=1440703232&sr=1-5&keywords=Jean-Marc+Savelli</ref>\n* [[Franz Liszt]] Rhapsodie hongroise No. 2\n\n2014 album \"The PIANIST of EMOTION\" on label \"KDM\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.mnet.interest.me/album/359895 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2015-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123081834/http://m.mnet.interest.me/album/359895 |archive-date=2015-11-23 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>https://www.amazon.fr/Classical-Recital-Jean-Marc-Savelli/dp/B00LBPM74U</ref><ref>https://www.genie.co.kr/detail/albumInfo?axnm=80453414</ref>\n[[Ludwig van Beethoven]], [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]], [[Andersen Viana]], [[Franz Liszt]]\n\nMusical works interpreted by Savelli are in French heritage within the [[National Library of France]] BNF.<ref name=\"data.bnf.fr\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n1981   Invited by [[Tino Rossi]] <ref>https://doc-14-1o-apps-viewer.googleusercontent.com/viewer/secure/pdf/26ank84sohj67791ulafelbljmg70fq2/tm74010vsibt6gr5kc5de3cs4q04v73l/1586182050000/drive/09855480875314119482/ACFrOgAalYCGIN9yCIXyjq6Q2l2kziKopvUEUXsLAhL8Rj-jNPuMFut--AiCTwdq6YQ2fK7te44ykdKkaNc-dqR5TIZvB17hPS-Jwt2SYjzKJJ5_ZrbxqNlJUB9t8JLwjQzyz2PBnfzvvzSuddZS?print=true&nonce=d78ivt4e4b16m&user=09855480875314119482&hash=mvhtj5u0gg4fv6icbfvndjrj673ajfat </ref>, in the television program Jacques Chancel's \"Great Chessboard\" on January 29, 1981, Jean-Marc Savelli interpreted  Sadness <ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1490460/?ref_=nmbio_bio_nm</ref> (Study Op. 10, n \u00b0 3, in E major) by [[Frederic Chopin]].\n\n\n2013  \"Corse Classique\" dedicated to [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], [[Franz Liszt]], [[Frederic Chopin]],<ref>{{YouTube|id=gXIChwW9vOA#t=148|title=\"Corse Classique\", clip video by Jean-Marc Savelli produced by the studio Ricordu}}</ref> voted best YouTube video about [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] by musicsense.org for the interpretation of Savelli in the 2nd and 3rd movement of the [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)|Piano Sonata No. 8]] of [[Ludwig van Beethoven]].\n\n==Bibliography==\n2020 \"French piano legends\"<ref>http://www.musicae.fr/livre-Les-Legendes-francaises-du-piano-de-Catherine-Lechner-Reydellet-226-135.html</ref>\nby [[Catherine Lechner-Reydellet]]<ref>https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catherine_Lechner-Reydellet</ref>\n\n\"French legends of the piano\" aux Editions [[Aedam Musicae]], published in 2020, is a work by [[Catherine Lechner-Reydellet]] [[writer]], and [[pianist]] dedicated to the memory of French pianists of the 20th century. Its vocation is to discover what the masters of the past have left to the great performers who succeeded them and in particular to decipher the technique of the ancients thanks to witnesses to French legends; we find Jean-Marc Savelli there through the heritage received from his masters [[Yvonne Lefebure]], [[Monique de La Bruchollerie]] and [[Pierre Sancan]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|france}}\n\n==links==\n*[http://www.musimem.com/prix-rome-1940-1949.htm Biographie Sancan]\n*[http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/ Official website JM SAVELLI]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Savelli, Jean-Marc}}\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:French classical pianists]]\n[[Category:French male pianists]]\n[[Category:Conservatoire de Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Mulhouse]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century classical pianists]]\n[[Category:21st-century French male musicians]]\n", "name_user": "Pratat", "label": "safe", "comment": "infobox corrections", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean-Marc_Savelli"}
